<section id="verify" class="section-block">
	<h2>2. Verify checksum (optional)</h2>
	<p>Validate file integrity by comparing SHA-256 checksums.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <strong>Windows PowerShell</strong>.</li>
		<li>Run: <code>Get-FileHash .\VoiceTel-3.5.6-Setup.exe -Algorithm SHA256</code></li>
		<li>Compare the output with the value listed above.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="install" class="section-block">
	<h2>3. Install</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Double-click the downloaded <strong>.exe</strong> or <strong>.msi</strong> file.</li>
		<li>If Windows SmartScreen appears, click <em>More info</em>, then <em>Run anyway</em>.</li>
		<li>Follow the installation wizard to complete setup.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="firstlaunch" class="section-block">
	<h2>4. First launch</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <strong>VoiceTel Phone</strong> from the Start Menu.</li>
		<li>Allow microphone access when prompted. If you missed the prompt, go to <em>Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; security &rarr; Microphone</em>, enable <em>Microphone access</em>, and allow <em>VoiceTel Phone</em>.</li>
		<li>Enter your VoiceTel SIP credentials (username, password, display name) as provisioned in the customer portal.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="faq" class="section-block faq-block">
	<h2>FAQ</h2>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>How do I uninstall or repair the app?</summary>
		<p>Open <em>Settings &rarr; Apps &rarr; Installed apps</em>. Locate <strong>VoiceTel Phone</strong> and choose <em>Uninstall</em> or <em>Modify/Repair</em> if available.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>What if audio doesn't work?</summary>
		<p>Check input/output devices in Windows Sound settings and verify microphone permissions are enabled.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Where can I find logs?</summary>
		<p>Logs are stored in <code>%APPDATA%\VoiceTelPhone\logs</code>. You can share them with support if needed.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Why does the installer request admin rights?</summary>
		<p>Admin privileges are required to register audio components and add VoiceTel Phone to the Start Menu.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can I install without admin rights?</summary>
		<p>Yes — use the portable executable (.exe) build above.</p>
	</details>
</section>

